1) Open SQL Server Management Studio and connect to the target SQL Server instance

2) Right-click on the Databases node and select Restore Database

3) Select Device and click on the ellipsis (...)

4) In the dialog, select Backup devices, click on Add, navigate to the database backup in
the file system of the server, select the backup, and click on OK.

5) If needed, change the target location for the data and log files in the Files pane
Note: It is a best practice to place the data and log files on different drives.

6) click on OK

7) This will initiate the database restore. After it completes
AdventureWorks database installed on SQL Server instance.
